rComments: This professor actually cares about his students. He will bell-curve exams, drop your worst assignmentquiz out of several. For this particular class there were a lot of assignments but in the end you realize it is just him trying to keep you prepared for the mid term and final. He is so kind and is always available via email and office hours.
Good prof. Straight-forward teaching. There is a lot of material in this course but he makes class interesting.

Great prof! This is a tough course, and he expects a lot so you have to work hard. He is good at explaining the material and he's approachable and very willing to answer questions in class or in office hours.

To be honest, he is a nice guy, however, I probably will not take another class with him in the future. He seriously needs to revise his marking scheme and be more engaging in lectures. The assignments and group project were very easy, but the final exam was confusing (and there were spelling mistakes).

Honestly a useless professor. Do not take any classes with him. Literally wants everyone to fail, does not care for part marks. Is extremely ignorant and rude. He should not be a professor. He is terrible and makes you feel dumb for asking questions. Worst professor ever.

How this man is allowed to teach at ANY level is beyond me. Tests, assignments, projects and so on do NOT at all reflect the material he was "teaching" us and he is so unclear. When my group asked about our project he was very rude and did not give proper feed back. He does not know how to teach, even though he is very knowledgable. AVOID.

Prof. Ksoll is terrible, I do not recommend his course. He is not fit to be a professor. He does not convey the subject matter well, and tests and assignments seem easy, but his marking scheme is bad, so most people do poorly. Don't expect any part marks on questions. If your answer is not exactly as his answer, you get a no marks.

This professor is absolutely useless. Do not take a class with him. He is highly educated but cannot teach. He hates answering questions and makes students feel silly for asking them. Expectations of students in the course are not clear. Assignments are not related to his teachings.
